docs.abstract: Hostilities between Israel and Palestinian militants in Gaza Strip resume after brief one-sided cease-fire generated by Egypt; Israelis scramble for shelter as more than 100 rockets descend on them and country retaliates with airstrikes that pound tunnels and rocket launchers in Gaza; Egypt's failed effort to halt hostilities reveals crucial differences from previous go-rounds that experts say make a resolution much more complicated to achieve.
